The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Wednesday, February 18, 2004  BUDDHADEB GUHA																				BUDDHADEB GUHA								Writer																																							Why not? Such a restriction has been enforced in some book fairs in the districts. You have to buy a book if you go in. This keeps the unwanted crowd away. After all, those fairs do not have an entry fee. The proposal can be given a try here as well. But it will be problematic to enforce the move. How can you check one lakh people at the gate? But it is true that sales are increasing.
